<Author>vicramasinger
<Content>WELL LOCATED Firstly this hotel is in an excellent location very close to sants train and metro station , it can be reached from the airport in 25 minutes.We booked on a stay 2 nights , 3rd night free deal which was excellent value. If you are planning on using the wi fi service then think again it costs 9 euros for 1 hour !! or 15 euros for 24 hours. A much better option is to use the internet cafe around the corner on carrer de numancia . It is very cheap at 1 euro per hour and is also very close to pans  co which is an excellent place to buy breakfast . it has a decent selection of small sandwiches and croissants , cakes etc ,excellent coffee and fresh orange juice. a typical breakfast of small ham and cheese ciabbatta , glass of freshly squeezed orange , coffee and cake would cost around 5 euros, which is a big saving on the 12 euro hotel breakfast.Barcelona is an excellent city for a short break, all the obvious sights are well worth a visit, if you intend to visit monjuic , the olympic stadium is free to enter and the olympic museum is worth a look at 3 euros i wouldnt bother with the cable car ride to the castle at the top of the hill. its a very short ride , it doesnt offer great views and is scandalously expensive . better to take your time and walk up or if thats not an option simply take a taxi from the metro station.If you visit sagrada familia (gaudi's cathedral) make sure you take the lift ride to the top of the tower it costs 2.50 euros but its a must.One last thing as in all big cities you have to watch your pockets and bags all the time , my advice would be leave the wallet in the hotel and just take whatever cash you minght need for the day.The metro is rife with petty thieves and pick- pockets that prey on tourists, I was talking to an english guy on the metro who was robbed whilst we were talking, neither of us saw a thing . !! they seem to operate in groups and when the metro is at its busiest.hope this review helps 
