<Author>Frank_ZA
<Content>NO non-smoking rooms... I read the reviews before I booked, but did not get the whole picture. The pics and info on the web look fine but I was disappointed:1. There were NO non-smoking rooms2. The room was small and odd shaped, which made matters worse.3. They are really stingy on the coffee at breakfast and you have to wait for the single, very elusive, kitchen staff to pop-in to the dining area before you can get coffee or a refill...very strange.4. A taxi drive to the Forum area at the sea-front costs about Euro 14 (Nov 2006). The train station, however, is only 2 blocks away. 
