<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>So-so, nothing special, nothing terrible The Hotel Abott is not old enough to be historically interesting and not new enough to be nice. Little TV, little bed, ok on cleanliness, slightly drab. Nothing about this hotel was especially good or bad, adequate. It is within walking distance of the subway but not in an area of interest to tourists. Your reason to stay here would be that you had business near by or wanted to be close to the train station (note that there are multiple train stations be sure what one you want) or you got a smoking deal. I don't say this place is terrible but as a tourist if I could do it again I would look elsewhere. 
