<Author>Angelfish'sMom
<Content>Not Thrilled We needed to stay over one night in Barcelona after departing our cruise before we could get a flight home. While the room rates were reasonable, there were many areas that were disappointing.We asked for two rooms (2 parents and children), however, they needed to give us three rooms because they could not accommodate our 2 children in one room. We were on different floors which made our kids uncomfortable. Further, 2 of the rooms did not have clean sheets, or if they were changed, there was still body hair etc on the sheets.While the rooms otherwise appeared clean, the air conditioning in one room only worked moderately. It was very hot and this was a much needed commodity. This property was close to the underground subway and was easy to reach Las Ramblas. It cost us 28 Euros to the airport (two cabs as there were 4 of us). I guess I am not accustomed to paying more than than the agreed upon price which was 20 Euros.Overeall, we should have paid the extra money and stayed in a more expensive hotel. Remember, only CNN is in english. 
